<br>
Realistically, skalds currently only add speed, an average damage chant, and very limited cc to a group.  The speed is on par with other realms.  The damage chant is not on par with other realms who utilize damage adds with higher dps.  Thankfully our chant has had its range expanded so that it is not useless.  The cc is almost worthless in light of realm abilities, and resists.  <br>
<br>
The other abilities of the skald are often not utilized, such as resist.  The resists are currently too specific and do not give you flexibility because they potentially overwrite casted resists from shaman or healers.  So once you turn that situational resist off and switch to another chant, it is gone from everyone in your group unless it is recasted.  <br>
<br>
I do not believe that the skald is in line with the original plan from Mythic due to changes in the game.  If Mythic wants to rectify these deficiencies, that would be nice.  If they want to add further group support abilities making the battlesong line more attractive, all the better.  Skalds should be different than a gimp warrior without a shield that has speed and two dd shouts.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.dravness.com/x.daoc/sig-sing.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=singdemsong>Singdemsong</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://camelot.dragonzones.com/sig/ns.jpg " BORDER=0> at: 10/14/03 6:58 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=seductroo>seductroo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 70<br> <font color=#ff0000>(10/14/03 7:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=734.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: sigh</span><hr size=1> Group enhancing benefits<br>
